2017: The Swedish Embassy is now trolling President Trump on Twitter Posted at 7:51 pm on February 19, 2017 by Greg P. 
And now we have the Swedish embassy in D.C. responding to President Trump, on Twitter, of course: We look forward to informing the US administration about Swedish immigration and integration policies. https://t.co/x5G3euOWRh 
— Embassy of Sweden US (@SwedeninUSA) February 19, 2017 
Welcome to 2017 where the world’s nations will battle it out in 140 characters or less: This has to be a first, right? https://t.co/FOtW5DQNOD 
— Travis Wright (@TalkinWright) February 20, 2017 The escalation of words between #Sweden and the U.S. is becoming sooo intense. https://t.co/GVWI7TkLnm 
— John Gushue (@JohnGushue) February 20, 2017 Wait, Twitter works both ways? #OUCH #HejaSverige
